<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC "-//Apple//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN" "http://www.apple.com/DTDs/PropertyList-1.0.dtd">
<plist version="1.0">
<dict>
	<!--
	  ============================================================
	  STATUS Apr 2026: NOT WIRED INTO BUILD.

	  This file exists but is *not* referenced by any Xcode target
	  (CODE_SIGN_ENTITLEMENTS is intentionally absent from
	  Runner.xcodeproj/project.pbxproj). The reason: the active
	  Apple Developer team for this project is a Personal (free)
	  team, which Apple does not allow to use the
	  `com.apple.developer.associated-domains` capability —
	  iOS Universal Links require a paid Apple Developer Program
	  membership ($99/yr).

	  HOW TO RE-ENABLE (after upgrading to a paid Developer Program):

	    1. In Xcode → Signing & Capabilities tab of the Runner
	       target, change the team from the Personal team
	       ("Viktorie Jiráková") to the paid team. Xcode will
	       auto-create a provisioning profile that includes
	       Associated Domains.

	    2. In `ios/Runner.xcodeproj/project.pbxproj`, add the line
	         CODE_SIGN_ENTITLEMENTS = Runner/Runner.entitlements;
	       inside ALL THREE Runner build configurations
	       (Debug / Profile / Release). They share the prefix
	       `ASSETCATALOG_COMPILER_APPICON_NAME = AppIcon;`
	       followed by `CLANG_ENABLE_MODULES = YES;` — that's the
	       anchor to grep for.

	    3. `flutter clean && flutter pub get && flutter run` from
	       checkfood_client. First launch will fetch the AASA from
	       https://checkfood-api-…/.well-known/apple-app-site-association
	       (already served by WellKnownController in checkfood_service).

	    4. Verify with `xcrun simctl openurl booted https://checkfood-api-…/api/auth/verify?token=test`
	       on the Simulator, or click a verification email link on
	       a real device — the app should open directly instead of
	       Safari.

	  No other code changes needed. The Flutter listener in
	  `lib/main.dart` (`_AppBootstrapperState._handleIncomingUri`)
	  is already wired and will start receiving events the moment
	  iOS sees the entitlement claim.
	  ============================================================

	  Tells iOS that this app is a valid handler for HTTPS URLs whose
	  host matches checkfood-api-809801655996.europe-central2.run.app
	  AND whose path matches one of the entries in the AASA file.
	-->
	<key>com.apple.developer.associated-domains</key>
	<array>
		<string>applinks:checkfood-api-809801655996.europe-central2.run.app</string>
	</array>
</dict>
</plist>
